#slide[
  ==== Potentiometer (WebSocket)

  / HTTP: becomes inefficient: polling repeatedly for a value that changes continuously wastes bandwidth and adds latency.
  / RESTful: polling would work but doesn't scale to real-time data.
  / WebSocket: solves it: one persistent connection, the ESP32 *pushes* new readings as they change — no repeated handshakes.
